\end{lemma}
\begin{proof}
  \uses{lem:injective_cech_acyclic, lem:cover_datum_bridge}
  \leanok
  A standard cover \(\mathcal{U}\) is a finite covering datum; by the covering-datum bridge
  (Lemma~\ref{lem:cover_datum_bridge}) its section {\v C}ech complex is identified with that of the
  corresponding finite open-cover object. The injective {\v C}ech-acyclicity
  Lemma~\ref{lem:injective_cech_acyclic} gives \(\check{H}^p(\mathcal{U}, \mathcal{I}) = 0\) for
  \(p > 0\) in the open-cover presentation, and the identification transports this vanishing back to
  the covering-datum form.
\end{proof}

